A man is missing at sea after saving a family member from drowning at the Pacaltsdorp beach in George in the Western Cape on Sunday afternoon (05/03/17). It is believed that the man was swept away by the tide and a search was currently underway for him ER24 spokesperson Annine Dormehl said. She said the 21-year-old man who nearly drowned was stabilised and transported to the George provincial hospital just after 3pm.. At the time of their arrival ER24 paramedics found the 21-year-old man on the beach surrounded by a crowd of people. Local authorities were on the scene for further investigations. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share